This recipe is to die for. Made it exactly as written, except instead of nice clean lamb shoulder I ended up with a hodgepodge of different lamb cuts. With all of the various bones, I decided to do a homemade 'lamb broth' in place of the chicken broth (basically the lamb bones, half an onion, a handful of peppercorns, a couple of cloves of garlic, and salt, with about 5c of water boiled down to 2c), and that worked out well. Followed others' suggestions of doubling the chickpeas, which I agree with, but then when it all came together I felt like more broth was needed. So added an extra cup of regular chicken broth. Anyway, the blend of flavours in this dish will blow your mind, and my only critique was that after an hour and a half, those chickpeas were looking a little soggy and crumbly. I might consider adding the chickpeas half way through the 1-hour simmering cycle.

