Rating: 4
This was a delicious and easy dinner for company. One of my guests had lived many years in Saudi Arabia, and said it was very authentic to the flavors she remembered. I worried it might be too sweet or spicy for some, but the flavors all melded together beautifully. I did chop the apricots into quarters, which worked well. And I had to use leg of lamb, since lamb shoulder was not available at my market. It was just perfect for a casual company dinner -- I had hardly any last minute work to do in the kitchen, so I could visit with my guests, instead! I served it with cous cous that had toasted almonds and scallions in it, which was a nice complement.

