My boyfriend's ex-wife is Moroccan. Perhaps the only thing he missed about her was the lamb dish her mother prepared while in Morocco. Per the suggestions of other reviewers, quartered the apricots and used canned diced tomatoes (the fresh ones are out of season and looked flavorless.) He said that this was not only the dish he had missed, but that this recipe was "even better." I particularly enjoyed how tender and flavorful the lamb turned out. Served with commercially-made Far East Pine Nut and Herb Couscous. A great cold weather dish to be made again and again.

