I'm a huge fan of all things lamb and Moroccan, and have just added this one to my repertoire after trying it yesterday. However, husband and I prefer a mixture of dried fruits such as figs and prunes, so next time may use these in lieu of the apricots, or in addition. I used a 4-1/2 quart Le Creuset Dutch oven for the whole operation, and find that tossing the lamb with olive oil after coating it with the seasoning provides a better result with the browning. Try this rather than pouring the oil into the pan.

